sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1366002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Genetic construct for lpp gen deletion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eduardo Cepeda Ca??edo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick contains the sequence homologies (50bp) to delete lpp gen (LPS moiety carrier) in E. coli with an ampicillin resistance and a Multiple Cloning Site (for the generation of genomic knock-ins of any desired gen in E. coli). The deletion of lpp gene and the replacement of that sequence with the Amp resistance. Gene deletions are performed with lambda-red recombination technology. FLP-FRT sequences are included to remove the antibiotic resistance with a specific recombinase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is the general structure 50bp homology Lpp // FRT // Amp R Promoter // RBS // AmpR // Terminator // FRT // MCS // 50 bp homology Lpp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The genetic design is based in the lpp deletion done by: Ni, Y., Reyes, J., & Chen, R. (2007). lpp Deletion as a Permeabilization Method. Biotechnology and Bioengineering, 1347-1356. It also contains some parts of the registry like BBa_K1073000, BBa_B0034, BBa_B0015
